article.headline: Lipscomb 67, Campbell 64
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Michael Lusk hit a 3-pointer with 13 seconds left to give Lipscomb a 67-64 win over Campbell Thursday night. Lipscomb (16-10, 10-5 Atlantic Sun Conference) trailed 64-62 with 1:56 left on a jumper by Campbell's Russ Gibson, then tied it on two free throws by Jason Hopkins with 1:06 left. Campbell (11-15, 6-10) made a turnover with two seconds left as the Camels had a chance to win or tie. Brian Fisk led Lipscomb with 18 points and six rebounds while reserve Michael Teller had 17 points and nine rebounds. Hopkins added 13 points. Jonathan Rodriguez scored 18 for the Camels and had six rebounds. Reggie Bishop scored 13 and Eric Smith had 12. Campbell led 31-26 at halftime and twice had nine-point leads early in the second half. Lipscomb controlled the boards 41-27.
